          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate the surplus of a budget rate. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
